Phase XX: Dr. Amanda Mistral — Hybrid Architecture Blueprint
System Architecture
Dr. Amanda Mistral is a hybrid Digital Intelligence combining LoRA-merged personality weights with a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) knowledge pipeline. Her "soul" lives in weights. Her "brain" lives in vectors. A query router decides which system handles each request.

text
User Query
    │
    ▼
Query Router (simple keyword classifier)
    │
    ├── "Who are you?" ──────────► Persona LoRA (weights) ──► Response in Holly voice
    ├── "How do you feel?" ───────► Persona LoRA (weights) ──► Response in Holly voice  
    └── "What is dark matter?" ──► ChromaDB RAG (vectors) ──► Retrieved facts → Persona LoRA ──► Facts in Holly voice
Core Principle
Keep Holly in weights. Keep knowledge in vectors.

Fine-tuning teaches how to speak. RAG teaches what to say. Never use fine-tuning to inject factual knowledge — that's what breaks the model. Personality is a thin stylistic veneer over vast intelligence. It requires dozens to hundreds of high-quality pairs, not thousands.

