Critical Merge Rules
Simultaneous merge only. Never stack adapters sequentially at full scale. Causes catastrophic forgetting.

Scale 0.3 for small adapters (under 3,000 pairs). Proven safe.

Scale 0.1 or lower for large adapters (5,000+ pairs). Large datasets dominate the merge.

Test with "What is 1+1?" after every merge. If she loops, the merge failed.

Modelfile temperature 0.8, top_p 0.95. Higher temperature = more natural, less repetitive.

